# ---------------------------------------------------------------
[stable]
version=1.4.4
url=https://albar965.github.io/release/2017/07/04/littlenavmap-stable-144-released.html
changelog=<ul>
   <li>Added light (Positron) and dark (Dark Matter) maps from CARTO.</li>
   <li>SimConnect is now detected and loaded dynamically.</li>
   <li>Added notification message if SimConnect was not found in connect dialog.</li>
   <li>The file link in the information window is now removed if the file cannot be found.</li>
   <li>Added start positions to runway information. These are also available if the airport has no runways.</li>
   <li>Improved aircraft progress display and fixed multiple omissions.</li>
   <li>Fixed problem with links in scenery database error dialog opening inline.</li>
   <li>Changed to Qt library 5.9. Note that the GTK style is not available anymore in Linux.</li>
   <li>P3D v4 runways, aprons and taxiways are now read correctly.</li>
   <li>Fixed crash with P3D v4 BGL files and crashes that appear after applying the P3D v4 hotfix 1.</li>
   <li>Added support for P3D v4 add-on.xml packages.</li>
 </ul>
downloadwin=https://github.com/albar965/littlenavmap/releases/download/v1.4.4/LittleNavmap-win-1.4.4.zip
downloadmac=https://github.com/albar965/littlenavmap/releases/download/v1.4.4/LittleNavmap-macOS-1.4.4.dmg
downloadlinux=https://github.com/albar965/littlenavmap/releases/download/v1.4.4/LittleNavmap-linux-1.4.4.tar.gz

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
[beta]
version=1.6.1.beta
downloadwin=https://www.magentacloud.de/lnk/6xFRU8hr
downloadmac=https://www.magentacloud.de/lnk/JElx0kia
downloadlinux=https://www.magentacloud.de/lnk/0nFRU6eG
changelog=
 <p><b>Changes from 1.6.0.beta to 1.6.1.beta</b></p>
 <p><i>The scenery database format has changed and the program will ask to erase its own databases if started.</i></p>
 <ul>
   <li>Adapted flight plan calculation, map display and information windows to
       one-way airways and maximum altitude restriction (X-Plane).</li>
   <li>Rhumb line measurement now shows both magnetic and true course where declination is based on origin.</li>
   <li>Improved weather display for nearest station: Added name, distance and map link to reporting station.</li>
   <li>Route string generation is now more robust for malformed and incomplete flight plans.</li>
   <li>Removed &quot;select nothing&quot; click areas in flight plan and procedure search top level labels.
       Added push buttons instead.</li>
   <li>Now erasing wrong airway entries at departure and destination when loading flight plan to avoid problems
       with malformed flight plans from PFPX.</li>
   <li>Fixed error where Documents path was not selected as default if missing simulator.</li>
   <li>Database loading dialog now pops up after erasing incompatible databases.</li>
 </ul>
 <small>
   <p><b>Changes from 1.5.4.develop to 1.6.0.beta</b></p>
   <ul>
     <li>Added display of nearest weather station for X-Plane metar file when showing information of an airport.</li>
     <li>ASP4 weather now supported.</li>
     <li>Changed handling of helipads and fixed display. Now using name as an identifier.</li>
     <li>Aircraft size is now displayed correctly for X-Plane on map and information window.</li>
     <li>Fixed problems with special characters in search (special characters are still treated case sensistive).</li>
     <li>Fixed problem where departure parking was dropped on certain cases like flight plan calculation.</li>
     <li>Fixed crash after copying airspaces.</li>
     <li>Added custom update dialog window that can display a longer message.</li>
     <li>Enabled database file exclusions and add-on override options to X-Plane loader. See options dialog on tab Scenery Library Database.</li>
     <li>Fixed crash when reading X-Plane add-on airports (KLAS).</li>
     <li>X-Plane file codec is now set to UTF-8 to avoid problems with special characters on Windows.</li>
     <li>Added detection of closed airports by name for X-Plane.</li>
     <li>Improved detection of military airports in general and name capitalization for X-Plane.</li>
   </ul>
   <p><b>Changes from 1.4.4 to 1.5.4.develop</b></p>
   <ul>
     <li>
       Full support for X-Plane 11:
       <ul>
         <li>scenery database: Airports, aprons, taxiways, navaids, airways, procedures, </li>
         <li>AI traffic, </li>
         <li>weather, </li>
         <li>copy airspaces from FSX/P3D to X-Plane database,</li>
         <li>FMS file loading/saving and</li>
         <li>moving map (needs included Little XpConnect plugin).</li>
       </ul>
     </li>
     <li>Automatic update check with settings in options dialog on tab startup.</li>
     <li>Speed limit for procedure segments.</li>
     <li>Fixed multiple problems with magnetic declination by using magdec.bgl file.</li>
     <li>Can now load FMS, FLP and FS9 ini-style PLN flight plan formats.</li>
     <li>Several problems fixed when loading FSX/P3D scenery databases and P3D v4 add-on.xml.</li>
     <li>Fixed missing encoding in saved PLN files.</li>
     <li>Shows startup positions now in the information window.</li>
     <li>Added clickspots in top labels to clear selections in procedure search and flight plan.</li>
     <li>Added donation link to help menu and about dialog (not active yet).</li>
   </ul>
 </small>

